# Career-Ops — Project Rules for Cursor IDE

> This file makes career-ops work natively in Cursor. It replaces the slash-command
> routing from Claude Code CLI with natural-language intent detection.
> For the full system docs, see `INSTRUCTIONS.md` (platform-agnostic) and `CLAUDE.md` (original).

---

## What Is career-ops

AI-powered job search pipeline: evaluate offers, generate ATS-optimized CVs, scan portals, track applications, prep for interviews — all driven by an AI agent reading your CV, profile, and proof points.

**740+ job listings evaluated · 100+ personalized CVs · 1 dream role landed**

---

## Session Start Checklist (run silently every session)

1. Check if `cv.md` exists
2. Check if `config/profile.yml` exists (not profile.example.yml)
3. Check if `modes/_profile.md` exists → if missing, copy from `modes/_profile.template.md`
4. Check if `portals.yml` exists (not templates/portals.example.yml)
5. Check if `data/applications.md` exists

**If ANY file is missing → enter onboarding mode** (see Onboarding section in `INSTRUCTIONS.md`).

After onboarding, run silently on first message:
```bash
node update-system.mjs check
```

Parse JSON output and notify if update available. Say nothing if up-to-date, dismissed, or offline.

---

## Intent Routing (replaces /career-ops slash commands)

Since Cursor doesn't have slash commands, detect the user's intent from their message and route to the appropriate mode. Load the specified files before executing.

### How to use career-ops in Cursor

Instead of `/career-ops scan`, the user just says what they want naturally:

| User says something like... | Mode | Files to load |
|-----------------------------|------|---------------|
| *Pastes a job URL or JD text* | `auto-pipeline` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/auto-pipeline.md` |
| "Evaluate this offer" / "Score this job" | `oferta` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/oferta.md` |
| "Compare these offers" / "Rank my options" | `ofertas` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/ofertas.md` |
| "Generate my CV" / "Create a PDF" / "Make my resume" | `pdf` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/pdf.md` |
| "Scan for jobs" / "Search portals" / "Find new offers" | `scan` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/scan.md` |
| "Process my pipeline" / "Check inbox" | `pipeline` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/pipeline.md` |
| "Help me apply" / "Fill application form" / "Apply to this" | `apply` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/apply.md` + `modes/auto-apply.md` |
| "Batch process" / "Evaluate all pending" | `batch` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/batch.md` |
| "Show tracker" / "Application status" | `tracker` | `modes/tracker.md` |
| "Research this company" / "Deep dive on..." | `deep` | `modes/deep.md` |
| "LinkedIn outreach" / "Draft message for..." | `contacto` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/contacto.md` |
| "Evaluate this course" / "Is this cert worth it?" | `training` | `modes/training.md` |
| "Evaluate this project idea" | `project` | `modes/project.md` |
| "Prep for interview at..." / "Interview prep" | `interview-prep` | `modes/_shared.md` + `modes/interview-prep.md` |
| "Analyze rejections" / "Why am I getting rejected?" | `patterns` | `modes/patterns.md` |
| "Show commands" / "What can you do?" / "Help" | `discovery` | Show the command menu (see below) |

### Auto-pipeline detection

If the user's message contains job description text (keywords: "responsibilities", "requirements", "qualifications", "about the role", "we're looking for") or a URL to a career page, automatically run the `auto-pipeline` mode — evaluate + report + PDF + tracker.

### Discovery menu

When the user asks for help or available commands, show:

```
career-ops — AI Job Search Command Center

Available actions (just tell me what you need):

• Paste a job URL or JD     → Full pipeline: evaluate + report + PDF + tracker
• "Evaluate this offer"     → A-F scoring evaluation only
• "Compare these offers"    → Rank multiple offers side-by-side
• "Generate my CV/PDF"      → ATS-optimized CV tailored to a role
• "Scan for jobs"           → Search 45+ company portals for matches
• "Process my pipeline"     → Evaluate pending URLs from data/pipeline.md
• "Help me apply"           → Fill application forms with AI-drafted answers
• "Batch process"           → Evaluate multiple offers sequentially
• "Show tracker"            → Application status overview
• "Research [company]"      → Deep company intel report
• "LinkedIn outreach"       → Find contacts + draft outreach message
• "Evaluate [course/cert]"  → Worth your time? Score against your goals
• "Evaluate [project idea]" → Portfolio project ROI analysis
• "Interview prep"          → STAR stories + company-specific intel
• "Analyze rejections"      → Pattern analysis to improve targeting

Your inbox: data/pipeline.md — add URLs and say "process my pipeline"
```

